<subSubSection pageId="51" pageNumber="52" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="51.[189,310,1155,1181]" box="[189,310,1155,1181]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,310,1155,1181]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,1155,1181]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="51.[189,1399,1201,1334]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
The species is most similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jussila" authorityYear="1965" box="[555,764,1201,1227]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Ophion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kevoensis">
<emphasis box="[555,764,1201,1227]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Ophion kevoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but has the face and head in anterior view narrower. Also similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Johansson" authorityName="Johansson &amp; Cederberg" authorityYear="2019" box="[380,719,1237,1263]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Ophion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sylvestris" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[380,588,1237,1263]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Ophion sylvestris</emphasis>
Johansson
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[729,823,1237,1263]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
but larger and with ovipositor sheath testaeous (black or dark brown in 
<taxonomicName authority="Johansson" authorityName="Johansson &amp; Cederberg" authorityYear="2019" box="[468,740,1272,1298]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Ophion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sylvestris" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[468,612,1272,1298]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">O. sylvestris</emphasis>
Johansson
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[746,840,1272,1298]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
). The barcoded specimens form two groups, but no morphological evidence supports the presence of two separate species at this point.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
